# 10-Data-Tables

## Mandates

### Reusable Components
- **All tables** must use TanStack Table (`@tanstack/react-table`) with the reusable components from `@/components/data-table`.
- **Never** build a table from scratch with raw `<Table>` + static `<TableHead>` markup. Always use TanStack Table with our reusable sub-components.

### Available Components (`src/components/data-table/`)
- `DataTable<TData, TValue>` — Generic wrapper. Accepts `columns`, `data`, `pageSize`, `pageSizeOptions`, `showPagination`.
- `DataTableColumnHeader` — Sortable/hideable column header with dropdown (Asc/Desc/Hide). Use for **every** column header.
- `DataTablePagination` — Full pagination: page size selector, first/prev/next/last buttons, page indicator, optional row selection count.
- `DataTableViewOptions` — Column visibility toggle dropdown. Add to toolbar area for tables with many columns.

### Usage Pattern
```tsx
import { DataTableColumnHeader, DataTablePagination, DataTableViewOptions } from "@/components/data-table"

// Column definitions — always use DataTableColumnHeader
const columns: ColumnDef<MyType>[] = [
  {
    accessorKey: "name",
    header: ({ column }) => <DataTableColumnHeader column={column} title="Name" />,
    cell: ({ row }) => row.original.name,
  },
]
```

### Styling Rules
- Wrap the `<Table>` in a `<div className="overflow-hidden rounded-md border">` container.
- Use default `CardContent` padding (`p-6 pt-0`). Never use `p-0` on CardContent and then add manual padding to children.
- Always include a "No results." empty row when filtered data returns zero matches.
- Default page size: **20 rows per page**.
- Page size options should include `20` (e.g. `[10, 20, 30, 50]`).

### Row Selection Count
- `DataTablePagination` auto-detects whether the table has a `select` column. If not, it hides the "X of Y row(s) selected" text.
- Override with `showSelectedCount={true|false}` prop if needed.

### Special Cases
- `src/components/data-table.tsx` (the drag-and-drop form builder table) is a **separate** component with DnD logic. Do not confuse it with the reusable `src/components/data-table/` directory.

### Reference Implementations
- `src/app/dashboard/competitions/[id]/athletes-tab.tsx` — Full example with search, dynamic columns, pagination, view options.
- `src/app/dashboard/competitions/[id]/athletes/[athleteId]/page.tsx` — Simpler example with sorting only.
